              <tr><td>Frames analyzed</td><td>212</td></tr>
            </table>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="section-title">Alignment</h3>
            <table>
              <tr><td>Topline mean / std (deg)</td><td>-40.93 / 12.61</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Saddle vs topline diff (deg)</td><td>199.15</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Withers clearance min/mean/std (px)</td><td>86.99 / 316.06 / 46.85</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Clearance collapse</td><td>No</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Bridging proxy</td><td>-14.71</td></tr>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card grid">
          <div>
            <h3 class="section-title">Symmetry (rider / saddle / horse)</h3>
            <table>
              <tr><td>Shoulder diff mean / std (px)</td><td>-220.66 / 138.21</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Hip diff mean / std (px)</td><td>157.76 / 94.62</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Lean consistency (std deg)</td><td>37.58</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Saddle roll proxy</td><td>232.82 (conf 17.4%)</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Horse topline std (deg)</td><td>12.61</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Confidence note</td><td>Side-view only; lateral symmetry not observed.</td></tr>
            </table>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="section-title">Gear & Safety</h3>
            <table>
              <tr><td>Status</td><td>WARN</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Notes</td><td>Consider breastplate for drift control.</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Recommendations</td><td>-</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Helmet</td><td>yes</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Boots</td><td>yes</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Pad</td><td>normal</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Girth</td><td>standard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Breastplate</td><td>no</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Crupper</td><td>no</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Stirrups</td><td>medium</td></tr>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card grid">
          <div>
            <h3 class="section-title">Marks (0-10) & How to Improve</h3>
            <table>
              <tr><td>Stability (10)</td><td>0.0 - Reduce rocking and drift to raise stability.</td></tr><tr><td>Alignment (10)</td><td>0.0 - Balance saddle to match topline and keep even contact.</td></tr><tr><td>Symmetry (10)</td><td>0.0 - Level shoulders/hips and equalize stirrup pressure.</td></tr><tr><td>Rhythm (10)</td><td>0.0 - Keep steady tempo; use metronome or poles if needed.</td></tr><tr><td>Clearance (10)</td><td>8.8 - Maintain withers clearance; adjust pad/tree if low.</td></tr><tr><td>Tracking (10)</td><td>1.7 - Film steady side view for higher tracking confidence.</td></tr><tr><td>Bounce (10)</td><td>0.2 - Engage core and follow motion to reduce bounce.</td></tr><tr><td>Drift (10)</td><td>1.6 - Check girth, pad grip, and straightness to limit drift.</td></tr>
            </table>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="section-title">Coaching</h3>
            <div class="label" style="margin-bottom:4px;">Doing well</div>
            <ul><li>Stable rocking across strides.</li><li>Withers clearance maintained through the ride.</li></ul>
            <div class="label" style="margin-top:8px;">To improve</div>
            <ul><li>Reduce vertical bounce by engaging core and following the motion.</li><li>Equalize weight in both stirrups to level shoulders/hips.</li><li>Improve saddle stability with tack adjustments or pad choice.</li></ul>
            <div class="label" style="margin-top:8px;">Drills</div>
            <ol><li>Posting trot with light contact: focus on even shoulder height for 30s intervals.</li><li>Two-point over ground poles to stabilize core and reduce bounce.</li><li>Ride straight lines with visual markers to monitor drift and alignment.</li></ol>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="section-title">Tracking Confidence & Video Quality</h3>
          <table>
            <tr><td>Tracking success (%)</td><td>17.4%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Frames processed</td><td>212</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Reinitializations</td><td>0</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Confidence note</td><td>Higher % means more reliable symmetry; side-view limits roll estimation.</td></tr>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="section-title">Riding Improvement Tips</h3>
          <p class="muted">Use these in your next session.</p>
          <ul><li>Review girth placement/tension and pad grip. Round-barrel horses may need stability solutions.</li><li>Coach note: work on even weight in both stirrups; ride straight lines and check saddle straightness.</li><li>Focus on core engagement and softer landing in the saddle to reduce bounce.</li><li>Cadence not detected (short video or limited motion); film 30-60s with consistent trot/canter for rhythm.</li><li>Rider level estimate: Beginner (17/100). Focus on steady shoulders/hips and straight lines.</li></ul>
        </div>
      </div>
